<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN322-intro">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. āvūr kiḻār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg style="pūṭṭuvil" xml:id="PN322">
<l>uḻutūr kāḷai yūḻkō ṭaṉṉa</l>
<l>kavaimuṭ kaḷḷip poriyaraip poruntip</l>
<l>putuvara karikāṟ karuppai pārkkum</l>
<l>puṉṟalaic ciṟāar villeṭut tārppiṟ</l>
<l>peruṅkaṭ kuṟumuyal karuṅkala ṉuṭaiya</l>
<l>maṉṟiṟ pāyum vaṉpulat tatuvē</l>
<l>karumpi ṉentirañ cilaippi ṉayala</l>
<l>tiruñcuval vāḷai piṟaḻu māṅkaṭ</l>
<l>ṭaṇpaṇai yāḷum vēntarkkuk</l>
<l>kaṇpaṭai yīyā vēlō ṉūrē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l>It is one of hard soil,</l>
<l>where, as the ruddy-headed boys lift [their] bows [and] shout,</l>
<l>when they join the mottled trunk of the Kaḷḷi with thorns forked</l>
<l>like the mature horns of the bull that creeps [home] after ploughing,</l>
<l>[and] look out for the wild rat in the stubble of new millet,</l>
<l>those with black ornaments, the huge-eyed small hares</l>
<l>  leap on the village common,</l>
<l>‒ in the village of the one with the spear who will not give rest</l>
<l>to the king who rules cool fields</l>
<l>in that place, where big-necked Vāḷai fish leap</l>
<l>in the neighbourhood when the sugarcane [juice] device resounds.</l>
<l>6+7b</l>
<l>huge-eyed small hares leap on the village common,</l>
<l>  so that black vessels break.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
